description:
You are a Quality Control Inspector at a consumer products company. Management is evaluating entry into three new product markets: (1) Portable space heaters, (2) Portable chargers / power banks, and (3) Children's sleepwear. Research recent CPSC product recalls for these categories using the CPSC Recalls database (https://www.cpsc.gov/Recalls) and SaferProducts.gov, identifying at least two specific recalls for each category. Organize your findings in a Firefox bookmark folder named 'Product Safety Research' containing at least six relevant bookmarks. Generate a structured JSON risk assessment report saved to '~/Documents/cpsc_risk_assessment.json' following this schema:

{
  "space_heaters": {
    "recalls_found": [
      {
        "recall_number": "XX-XXX",
        "product_name": "...",
        "hazard": "...",
        "recall_date": "YYYY-MM-DD",
        "manufacturer": "..."
      }
    ],
    "common_hazards": ["..."],
    "risk_level": "high|medium|low"
  },
  "power_banks": { ... },
  "childrens_sleepwear": { ... }
}
